To test the analytical performance of the fabricated immunosensor, EIS measurements were carried out by the detection of different PSA concentrations under optimal conditions. As shown in Fig. 5
                         (a and b), it was found that the changes in the measured impedance were proportional to the PSA concentration in the range 1–10000 pg/mL. As expected, the values of RCT showed a linear increase in the presence of different concentrations of PSA. The linear regression equation was obtained as ΔRCT (Ω) = 1226.7 × log CPSA (pg/mL) + 470.72 (R2 = 0.9997), with the low detection limit (LOD) of 0.48 pg/mL (3Sb/m). The proposed immunosensor exhibits satisfactory performance with those of other PSA immunoassays reported (Table 2
                        ).
